<Layout>
  <article class="blog-post">
    <header class="post-header">
      <h1>Lunar Eclipse 2025 - Blood Moon</h1>
      <time datetime="2025-07-28">September 08, 2025</time>
      <p class="post-intro">
        The moon turned a deep shade of red. A rare Blood Moon that I was
        fortunate to capture through my lens.
      </p>
    </header>

    <figure class="post-image">
      <img
        src="/images/blog/sky&beyond/Lunar-eclipse-2025/img1.webp"
        alt="Lunar Eclipse 2025"
      />

      <figcaption>Lunar Eclipse 2025</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <section class="post-content">
      <p>
        The sky was quiet, the air still, and the moon slowly slipped into
        Earth's shadow, bathing the night in a deep crimson glow. Its
        transformation was gradual yet mesmerizing, shifting from soft orange to
        a rich, almost haunting red. Watching it unfold felt like witnessing a
        secret performance in the heavens.
      </p>

      <p>
        Through my lens, capturing the Blood Moon was a delicate dance of
        patience and timing. Each moment demanded careful exposure adjustments
        and steady focus to preserve the intensity of its color while keeping
        the surrounding sky subtle and mysterious. Every click of the shutter
        felt like holding a fleeting piece of the universe in my hands.
      </p>

      <figure class="post-image small-img">
        <img
          src="/images/blog/sky&beyond/Lunar-eclipse-2025/img2.webp"
          alt="Camera Image Lunar Eclipse"
        />
        <figcaption>Camera Image Lunar Eclipse</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>
        This celestial spectacle reminded me that nature's wonders aren't
        confined to forests or lagoons. Sometimes, the most breathtaking stories
